{{Dialogue|R2-D2|line1=no|[beeps]|C-3PO|R2 says it's some kind of sleeping virus that only affects Humans.|Chewbacca|line3=no|[growls lowly]|C-3PO|He says the only way to keep them alive is to let the blood rush through their heads.|attr=C-3PO translating for R2-D2 and Chewbacca to Boba Fett|src=<ref name="Wook" />}}
The '''sleeping virus''', also referred to as the '''talisman virus''' was a virus that only [[Human/Legends|Humans]] could catch, and put its victims into a [[Coma/Legends|comatose]] state. A [[Serum (sleeping virus)|serum]] existed to cure the virus.

==Description==
{{Quote|I know this sleeping virus the Empire uses on its enemies. They have a remedy for it in the city.|Boba Fett|<ref name="Wook" />}}
The [[Sleep/Legends|sleeping]] virus was designed by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and exclusively affected [[Human/Legends|Humans]], who would become [[Coma/Legends|comatose]] when infected. Victims could be hung upside-down to let [[Blood/Legends|blood]] rush to their heads to extend their chances of survival. A [[Serum (sleeping virus)|serum]] to cure the virus was commercially available, though patients were still groggy for some time after initial treatment<ref name="Wook" />

==History==
{{Quote|Starlog update: Although Boba Fett quickly located the serum for the sleeping virus, we had no idea of his real plan.|Captain Kazan|<ref name="Wook" />}}
[[File:SleepingVirus.jpg|thumb|left|200px|[[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] under the influence of the virus.]]
The virus was created by the Empire for use against its enemies. The [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] was familiar with the virus and that a remedy was available. The sleeping virus was planted on a [[Talisman (artifact)|talisman]], which was rumoured to have the power to render objects invisible.<ref name="Wook" /> Between [[0 ABY/Legends|0.5 ABY]] and [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]]<ref name="Date">''[[The New Essential Guide to Characters]]'' places the [[Mission to Panna Prime|mission]] to [[Panna Prime]] after the [[Evacuation of Yavin]], which it also placed six [[Standard month/Legends|months]] after the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], corresponding to [[0 ABY/Legends|0.5 ABY]] according to ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''. {{SW|url=news/the-best-holidays-and-celebrations-in-the-galaxy-everybodys-invited-of-course|text=The Best Holidays and Celebrations in the Galaxy&hellip;and Empire Day, Too|int=The Best Holidays and Celebrations in the Galaxy&hellip;and Empire Day, Too|nolive=1}} mentions that ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'' was one [[Standard year/Legends|year]] after the Battle of [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin]], corresponding to [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]]. Therefore, the events of the mission as portrayed in ''[[The Story of the Faithful Wookiee]]'' must have occurred between 0.5 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]] and 1 ABY.</ref> during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] between the Empire and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], the talisman was sought by both factions for its alleged power. [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] of the Alliance recovered it,<ref name="Wook" /> having been allowed to do so by Fett,<ref name="Data">{{DB|character|bobafett|Fett, Boba}}</ref> and the Human Solo quickly succumbed to its effects. [[Gender/Legends|His]] [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] companion tied Solo upside-down inside their [[Starship/Legends|starship]], the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], on their return to a Rebel [[Ring Base|base]]. The ''Falcon'' nearly crashed into the base, but Chewbacca steered away so it instead crash-landed on the [[Moon/Legends|moon]] [[Panna Prime]].<ref name="Wook" />

Solo and Chewbacca's friend [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], accompanied by the [[Droid/Legends|droids]] [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] and [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], undertook a [[Mission to Panna Prime|mission]] to Panna Prime. There, joined by Fett, who was on a secret mission to find the Rebel base for the Empire, they found the ''Falcon'' and discovered Chewbacca destroying the talisman. Skywalker shouted for him to stop, but was quickly infected by the virus and collapsed. C-3PO and R2-D2 realized that the talisman had spread the virus and explained its spread and Chewbacca's method of treatment to Fett. The bounty hunter revealed that he knew the serum to treat it could be found in [[Panna City]], and Chewbacca joined him to go retrieve it. Fett quickly found the serum in a shop, but before acquiring it contacted the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] to inform him of his progress in gaining the Rebel's trust. Afterwards Fett gained the serum and returned to the ''Falcon'' with Chewbacca and revived Skywalker and Solo,<ref name="Wook" /> who was so dazed from the virus that he did not recognize Fett desipte a previous encounter.<ref name="Characters">''[[The Essential Guide to Characters]]''</ref> After Skywalker offered for Fett to join the Rebels at their base, C-3PO and R2-D2 revealed their knowledge of Fett's true allegiance, and that the whole affair had been an Imperial plot. The events of the mission were later portrayed in a [[Unidentified Rebel cartoon|cartoon]] for the Rebel Alliance, narrated by [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Kazan]].<ref name="Wook" />

==Behind the scenes==
The sleeping virus appeared in ''[[The Story of the Faithful Wookiee]]'', a cartoon<ref name="Wook" /> written by [[George Lucas]] and produced by [[Nelvana]] Studios.<ref name="Tooning Out">{{SWArchive|url=movies/saga/20081210.html|text=Tooning Out the "Holiday Special": Nelvana Studios}}</ref> It originally aired on television in [[1978]] as part of ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''.<ref name="Holiday Special">''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''</ref>

